{
  "stem": "490.1",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So to ask, how was the holidays, holidays was the thing people were living for.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "This was the only entertainment.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The only pleasure they got out of life [BACKGROUND NOISE] was these holidays, these gathering of people, and to celebrate together with friends or with relatives.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So it was a way of life.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It was not just a-- a tradition, like we-- we know it today, that we observe this or we observe that.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We were looking forward for these holidays.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And it was a-- the biggest part of the Jewish life.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "What was your experience of anti-Semitism before the war?",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "This is a very-- I suppose it is known, but people don't talk about it.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "My first [PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] problem with-- with physical-- physical problem with-- from-- which I-- occurred to me was not from the Germans but from the Poles.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I had my nose broken, walking in the street at the wrong time.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Because I had to go a little in the dark, so people shouldn't see me, from the Germans.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But I didn't think that a Pole will pass by.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And he didn't like me because he thought-- he knew he was-- I was Jewish.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Then he just broke my nose, for no reason at all.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "[BACKGROUND NOISE] Well, this might-- might have been a-- one incident that happened to me.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "But it also happened to-- to the system.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "After the occupation, the Germans did not know the difference between a Pole and a Jew.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "It is the Poles who let them in, the Poles who told them that this is a Jew and this is not a Jew.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "It is unfortunate if this sounds a little too-- there are certain things in life that-- it is true, but you don't talk about it.",
      "word_count": 25
    }
  ],
